---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import { STATS, PILLARS, QIF_BANDS } from '../lib/qif-constants';
---

<PageLayout
  title="About — Qinnovate"
  description="Qinnovate is Kevin Qi's research initiative mapping the security threats facing brain-computer interfaces, scoring their neural impact, and publishing everything openly."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'About' }]}
>
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-8">About</h1>

    <div class="prose">
      <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed mb-8">
        Qinnovate is my research initiative. I map the security threats facing brain-computer interfaces, score their neural impact, and publish everything openly. The work sits at the intersection of cybersecurity, neuroscience, and ethics.
      </p>

      <h2>What I Build</h2>
      <p>
        Three interlocking frameworks that together map how neurotechnology can be secured, validated, and governed:
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4 my-8 not-prose">
      {PILLARS.map((pillar) => (
        <a href={pillar.href} class="glass rounded-xl p-5 card-hover group">
          <div class="text-xl mb-2" style={`color: ${pillar.color}`} set:html={pillar.icon} />
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] mb-1 group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] transition-colors">
            {pillar.name}
          </h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mb-2">{pillar.tagline}</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">{pillar.description}</p>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Mission</h2>
      <p>
        Brain-computer interfaces are advancing faster than the security standards to protect them. Neuralink has implanted its N1 chip in human patients. Synchron's Stentrode is in FDA-approved clinical trials. Blackrock Neurotech has shipped Utah arrays for over a decade. Commercial EEG headsets from Emotiv, Muse, and OpenBCI sit on consumer shelves. These devices are tested for safety and efficacy. There is no standardized public framework to validate their resistance to adversarial threats. No standardized framework exists to classify, score, or mitigate attacks on the human brain.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's the gap I'm closing — developing the security specifications, threat models, and scoring metrics that the BCI industry needs before these devices reach mass adoption.
      </p>

      <h2>The Framework</h2>
      <p>
        QIF is an open, peer-reviewable security framework for brain-computer interfaces. It bridges two domains that don't normally talk to each other:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cybersecurity</strong> — Layered defense models, threat taxonomies, attack surface analysis, and scoring systems (CVSS, STRIDE)</li>
        <li><strong>Neuroscience</strong> — Neuroanatomy, neural signaling pathways, clinical outcomes, and the DSM-5-TR diagnostic framework</li>
        <li><strong>Clinical medicine</strong> — Therapeutic applications, FDA regulatory mapping (FDORA Section 3305), DSM-5-TR diagnostic outcomes, and ICD-10-CM coding for neural impact</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The result is the <strong>Hourglass Model</strong>: an 11-band, 3-zone architecture with the Neural Interface (I0 — the physical BCI device) at its waist. Biology above. Silicon below. The <a href="/TARA/">TARA Atlas</a> maps 102 techniques across this hierarchy, each scored with NISS (Neural Impact Scoring System) and mapped to DSM-5-TR diagnoses through the Neural Impact Chain.
      </p>

      <h2>Approach</h2>
      <p>
        Everything is open: open publication, transparent methodology, publicly available framework documents, equations, and reference implementations. Neural security research must be developed in the open — not behind closed doors. The people whose brains will be connected deserve to understand exactly how they're protected.
      </p>
      <p>
        These governance documents represent the values I believe any future BCI security standard should uphold.
      </p>

      <h2>About Me</h2>
      <p>
        I'm <strong>Kevin Qi</strong>, an independent security researcher. I developed QIF from first principles, beginning with a simple question: <em>what does the OSI model look like when one endpoint is a brain?</em>
      </p>

      <h2>Milestones</h2>
      <p>
        QIF was derived from first principles in 7 days of formal derivation — 50 log entries, 4 framework versions, from zero techniques to a complete stack. Every breakthrough, every dead end, every pivot is documented.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="/about/milestones/" class="text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] hover:text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)] transition-colors font-medium">View the full derivation timeline &rarr;</a>
      </p>

      <h2>Publications</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="glass rounded-xl p-5 sm:p-6 my-6 not-prose" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent-tertiary);">
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-4">
        <div class="flex-1">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.12em] uppercase text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)] mb-1.5">Zenodo Preprint &middot; Feb 2026</p>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)] leading-snug mb-1">
            Securing Neural Interfaces: Architecture, Threat Taxonomy, and Neural Impact Scoring for Brain-Computer Interfaces
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)]">
            Kevin Qi &middot; 27 pages, 6 figures &middot; CC-BY 4.0 &middot; DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.18640105" class="text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">10.5281/zenodo.18640105</a>
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-2 shrink-0">
          <a href="/papers/qif-bci-security-2026.pdf" class="px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)] text-white font-medium text-sm hover:opacity-90 transition-opacity text-center" target="_blank">
            PDF
          </a>
          <a href="https://zenodo.org/records/18640105" class="px-4 py-2 rounded-lg glass text-[var(--color-text-primary)] font-medium text-sm hover:bg-black/5 transition-colors text-center" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
            Zenodo
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose">
      <h2>Open Standard</h2>
      <p>
        QIF is not a proprietary product. It's an open framework, freely available for researchers, device manufacturers, regulators, and security professionals to adopt, extend, and critique.
      </p>

      <div class="glass rounded-xl p-6 my-8 not-prose">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-6 text-center">
          <a href="/whitepaper/" class="group">
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">{STATS.frameworkVersion}</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-1 group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent-primary)] transition-colors">Framework</div>
          </a>
          <a href="/news/" class="group">
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)] group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">{STATS.publications}</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-1 group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent-secondary)] transition-colors">Publications</div>
          </a>
          <a href="/framework/" class="group">
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-status-safe)] group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">{QIF_BANDS}</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-1 group-hover:text-[var(--color-status-safe)] transition-colors">Security Bands</div>
          </a>
          <a href="/licensing/" class="group">
            <div class="text-2xl font-bold font-[family-name:var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)] group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform">Open</div>
            <div class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-faint)] mt-1 group-hover:text-[var(--color-accent-tertiary)] transition-colors">License</div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
